Package au.csiro.pathling

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Configuration
    Defines all the configuration options for the Pathling server.
    Configuration.Async
    Represents configuration relating to asynchronous processing.
    Configuration.Authorization
    Represents configuration specific to authorization.
    Configuration.Authorization.Ga4ghPassports
    Configuration relating to support for GA4GH Passports as a method of authorization.
    Configuration.Cors
    Represents configuration relating to Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS).
    Configuration.Encoding
    Represents configuration specific to FHIR encoding.
    Configuration.HttpCaching  
    Configuration.Import
    Represents configuration specific to import functionality.
    Configuration.Spark
    Represents configuration that controls the behaviour of Apache Spark.
    Configuration.Storage
    Configuration relating to the storage of data.
    Configuration.Storage.Aws
    Configuration relating to storage of data using Amazon Web Services (AWS).
    Configuration.Terminology
    Represents configuration specific to the terminology functions of the server.
    PathlingServer
    Main class that serves as the entry point for running the Pathling server.
    PathlingServerListener
    Performs any required actions on startup of the application.
    PathlingVersion
    Retrieves version information from the properties file created during the build, making it available to other areas of the application.
    QueryExecutor
    Contains functionality common to query executors.
    QueryExecutor.FhirPathAndContext  
    QueryHelpers
    Common functionality for executing queries using Spark.
    QueryHelpers.DatasetWithColumn
    Represents a Dataset along with a Column that can be used to refer to one of the columns within.
    QueryHelpers.DatasetWithColumnMap
    Represents a Dataset along with a map between two sets of columns.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    QueryHelpers.JoinType
    Represents a type of join that can be made between two Dataset objects.
